sentences: Joseph Kirkland (born April 5, 1968), better known by his stage name Diamond D, is an American hip hop MC and record producer from The Bronx, New York City, and one of the founding members of the Diggin' in the Crates Crew, abbreviated as D.I.T.C.
At the beginning of his career as a producer, Diamond spent many hours at Jazzy Jay's studio on Allerton Avenue in The Bronx.
In a 2017 interview he said, "I learned about 95% of my production skills from him.
The following year he released his debut record Stunts, Blunts and Hip Hop.
In a 2017 interview Diamond described the album as, "just a collection of beats and records I was just setting aside.
It was more about, 'One day I want to do something with this' ideas.
It took him 30 minutes to construct the beat one of the album's best-known tracks, "Sally Got A One Track Mind".
In 1996 Diamond won a Grammy Award for his production on the title track from The Fugees' The Score album.

To promote his 1997 sophomore record Hatred, Passions and Infidelity, Mercury Records compiled a promotional vinyl called Diamond Jewels that included the Stunts, Blunts, and Hip Hop songs "Best Kept Secret', "*!
